                    "ability_type": "offensive",
                    "action_type": {
                        "type": "stat_block_section",
                        "subtype": "action_type",
                        "name": "Two Actions"
                    },
                    "frequency": "once per hour",
                    "effect": "You sing, hum, or whistle a note, and your bow provides appropriate accompaniment. Make a Strike with the bow. If it hits, the bow generates a magical effect determined by the note you sung, which has the traits indicated in parentheses. This affects every creature in a 10-foot emanation from the creature you hit. As normal for an emanation, you choose whether the creature you hit is affected. \n* **Song of Soothing** (emotion, enchantment, healing, mental) Each creature regains 3d10 Hit Points and gains a +1 status bonus to saves against mental effects for 1 minute.\n* **Song of Suffering** (evocation, sonic) Each creature takes 3d10 sonic damage with a DC 31 basic Fortitude save.",
